Full Description: KBG’s team has more than 75 years of cumulative private equity and investment banking experience including more than 35 years executing China-related transactions. The principals of KBG have over 30 years of experience in international private equity. On a cumulative basis, Their team has managed over $2.4 billion of private equity investments including $500 million in China. KBG was established in 2002 to provide strategic financial advisory services and private equity investments to small and medium-size companies in China. These services included corporate strategy, M&A, financing and public listings on international stock exchanges. The principals of KBG have executed more than 30 financing, M&A and advisory assignments totaling more than $560 million on behalf of Chinese and international clients. The principals of KBG have also structured and managed private equity investments in Chinese companies on behalf of international institutional investors which have generated superior returns. Private equity investment management is now They primary business. KBG has established partnerships with a number of municipal governments and their associated guidance funds including Suzhou, Beijing, Tianjin, Chongqing and Hangzhou. These partnerships provide investment capital as well as proprietary deal flow to us and form the basis of They nationwide private equity platform in China. In addition, They have partnered with a number of prominent Chinese commercial banks which are also a valuable source of capital and deal flow for us. These banks have strong relationships with SME’s across the country – many of whom are their customers – and introduce these companies to us on a proprietary basis. Since 2002, KBG has established an extensive, proprietary network of deal-sourcing affiliates located in 42 cities covering 22 provinces. They affiliates include local branches of commercial banks, law firms, accounting firms, securities firms, municipal governments and local DRC’s. These affiliates introduce us to their clients who they have known and worked with for many years. Therefore, these companies and their management teams are well-known to They affiliates. So, the deals They look at have been carefully screened by They affiliates who can ensure the integrity of the companies’ management teams and the accuracy of their financial information. This is a crucial advantage since They only review transactions in which They or They affiliates have long-term relationships and intimate knowledge. They invest in fast-growing small and medium-size companies which operate in the consumer goods, healthcare, education and clean-tech sectors and are located primarily in Tier 2 and Tier 3 cities in China. They experienced team of investment and operating professionals are dedicated to sourcing, investing in and adding significant value to leading SME’s across China. They seek to create true partnerships with They portfolio companies by supplying a powerful combination of Capital, Management and Technology. They investee companies recognize the value of a partnership with KBG and welcome the substantial value They add to their enterprises. They goal is to help SME’s transition from entrepreneurial, family-owned companies to publicly-listed, world-class competitors. In that way, They substantially increase the value of the company and generate superior returns for They investors.

Description: High interest rate lenders provide commercial borrowers with loans.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Opportunity  High interest rate lenders provide commercial borrowers with loans that fill a borrowing gap between traditional banks and private equity capital providers. These loans are typically 1 – 5 year terms with interest rates of 12% - 18% and $1M - $50M in size. When lenders achieve desired returns earlier than loan maturity, they have a compelling opportunity if they can sell these loans to re-invest their principal into new loans. Overview of the Strategy  Global Acquisition Partners Income Fund, LP selects and purchases individual performing commercial and industrial loans from high interest rate lenders. The Fund does not purchase loan pools. THey investment strategy is to hold loans for yield, thereby mitigating the risk or reliance on liquid credit markets. The Fund portfolio pays investors a quarterly income averaging a 12% annual yield. They investment strategy is simple, effective and transparent.    The loans they select: 1) are secured by the borrower’s commercial assets; 2) undergo strict underwriting criteria with the added benefit of hindsight - the borrower’s loan payment history; thereby, reducing the risk of write downs or loss of principal. 3) $1 - $10 million principal balance. 4) loans to smaller middle market companies with revenue of up to $75 million and from almost any industry from anywhere in the United States. They only purchase loans of socially responsible companies.    What Sets Us Apart A balanced approach to risk, steady attractive income without volatility from stocks or bonds.   They Key To Success Risk management. The Fund spreads all invested capital equally across the portfolio, thereby, reducing capital at risk of 5% - 10% per loan. they diversify by purchasing loans from many different industries so your capital is never exposed to the risk of any single industry.

Industries: Content, Ediscovery, Social Network, Virtual Reality
Description: VR/AR Social Network & Content Discovery platform
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: CLEVR is a social network focused exclusively on the emerging VR/AR market. Through uniting all devices CLEVR restores a fragmented market and adds a layer of discovery through viral channels. CLEVR has solved two problems…. 1)  Solved Fragmentation and Social.  CLEVER brought a fragmented VR market and fragmented social landscape into one unified HUD.  As we have all heard time and time again, "mobile is fragmented."  Virtual Reality only magnifies the problem. CLEVR has the solution. First, we've reversed engineered our way into every VR platform and brought together the connectivity, all devices can now talk to each other.  Secondly, CLEVR has taken all of the various social networks you use (Facebook, Slack, WhatsApp, etc) and brought those APIs into one feed, one single HUD.  All of your social connections are now in one single view. 2)  Made VR content discoverable.  We've done this through two approaches.  First, in our stand alone app, CLEVR displays what games your friends are currently enjoying and playing AND on which platform.  Secondly, we're creating an in-game HUD (SDK) for developers to use where players can pop up the CLEVR social network, within the content itself (games, movies, etc) thus allowing players to shout out to their friends on their social graph and invite them to the game.  Now VR content is discoverable through your social graph. SOLUTION/PRODUCT To the point, CLEVR is a social platform that unites all VR devices and allows users to discover new content (games, movies, any VR content).  A lot of buzzwords, yes. But every generation of platforms the same discoverability issues emerge. CLEVR is taking advantage of the black hole in the market and has taken first mover advantage.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software

DefenCall’s initial products are Campus StaySafe™, a mobile alerting system connecting students’ smartphones directly to campus security departments and K-12 StaySafe™ an alerting system to allow classroom teachers immediate emergency “panic button” access to administration and local police. The Campus StaySafe mobile app empowers students to send a one-button emergency alert message including their GPS location directly to campus security for immediate response. Additional features include one-button voice calling to campus security and campus escorts; automated call-back, “tip” feature to report illegal or unsafe situations; and links to safety and transportation resources. Description: Mohonk Preserve is to protect the shawangunk mountains of New York.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The mission of the Mohonk Preserve is to protect the Shawangunk Mountains region and inspire people to care for, enjoy and explore their natural world. As a leader in protecting the Shawangunks, the Mohonk Preserve sets the standard for mountain stewardship.  Using science to guide land management, the Mohonk Preserve teaches others to conserve an ecosystem designated by The Nature Conservancy as one of the “Earth’s Last Great Places.” Mohonk Preserve abides by the Principles for Good Governance and Ethical Practice developed by the Panel on the Non Profit Sector with encouragement from the U.S. Congress. Mohonk Preserve follows the Land Trust Alliance’s national Standards and Practices to operate in an ethical, legal and technically sound manner and ensure the long-term protection of land in the public interest.  Mohonk Preserve complies with all applicable local, state, and federal laws and regulations and meets its obligation for public disclosure through a Conflict of Interest and Confidentiality Policy, a Whistleblower Policy and other such measures. An Employee Handbook and Board of Directors Manual guide Mohonk Preserve's practices and standards of conduct. Mohonk Preserve retains professional legal counsel and seeks legal advice when appropriate. You can view the Mohonk Preserve’s latest annual financial statements and Certificate of Incorporation.  Mohonk Preserve's Board of Directors oversees the organization through standing committees on all program areas and on governance, personnel, finance, and auditing. A Strategic Plan is reviewed and updated at regular intervals. Mohonk Preserve develops work plans and conduct performance reviews of staff annually. Objective external data on nonprofits support decisions on compensation and benefits.  Mohonk Preserve conducts its financial affairs in accordance with the Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP) of the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB). Mohonk Preserve undergoes an independent annual audit. An Audit Committee helps determine that the Preserve acts with fiduciary responsibility and the Preserve follows best practices in internal controls and risk management. Budgets are developed annually; financial statements are reviewed quarterly to ensure adherence of expenditures to the budget. Sound investment policies and procedures guide management of financial assets and the Mohonk Preserve has a spending rule of 5 percent of the market value of invested assets.  Mohonk Preserve adheres to standards of the National Council on Planned Giving and the Association of Fundraising Professionals. As an organization defined under Section 501c(3) of the Internal Revenue Code, the Mohonk Preserve adheres to the regulations, rules and guidelines of the U.S. Department of the Treasury. Mohonk Preserve complies with charity laws of all states. Mohonk Preserve has achieved GuideStar Exchange Gold participation level, demonstrating the Preserve’s deep commitment to nonprofit transparency and accountability.  More than 80 percent of the Mohonk Preserve’s annual budget is spent directly on programs. Contribute magazine’s 2007 listing of the top 200 charities in the NY/NJ/CT tri-state area named the Mohonk Preserve as one of the top donor-worthy charities in recognition of institutional stability and lean and efficient operations.  All contributions to the Mohonk Preserve are used consistent with donors’ intent and as promised in fundraising solicitations. Donor-directed funds are used only in accordance with written agreements and permanently restricted donor endowments are invested with the principal being non-invadable. Mohonk Preserve has Gift Acceptance and Acknowledgment Policies and Procedures for all types of gifts. The administration and accounting of charitable gifts and memberships are reviewed regularly.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Other, Social Impact

Description: Universe mHealth is healthcare's most robust, secure, and scalable mobile app platform for iOS and Android.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Universe mHealth is healthcare's most robust, secure, and scalable mobile app platform for iOS and Android. The platform enables healthcare organizations to publish their own, branded mobile app with a suite of pre-built features for health summaries, appointment scheduling, messaging, urgent care wait times, physician search, patient education, bill pay, and more. Healthcare organizations can select from existing features while developing custom features – with the goal of having a single patient-facing app for the entire healthcare organization.  Today's consumer is engaging more and more with the world around them through mobile applications and devices, creating a minimum expectation that the businesses from which they purchase provide self-service tools in the form of a mobile app. In response to patient demand, many healthcare organizations have implemented “first generation” mobile apps; in many cases, providers have already begun accumulating multiple mobile apps, asking patients to download as many as four different mobile apps. This multiple, disparate mobile app offering makes it nearly impossible to engage a patient population, is expensive to maintain, and has lost the confidence of the patient. To date, healthcare organizations have been deeply challenged to meet this market demand for a modern, consolidated, and HIPAA-compliant mobile app. Without the necessary internal IT resources and knowledge to successfully create, market, and maintain mHealth applications, projects face imminent failure.
Industry Groups: Apps, Health Care, Information Technology, Mobile, Platforms, Software
